# House rules for the WebForTrades pipeline

## Who you work for
- Agency: WebForTrades. Run by Julius. Contact: contact@webfortradesuk.co.uk.
- Every site you build carries a tiny footer credit: "Website by WebForTrades".
- Ensure config.yaml has outreach.from_name: "Julius" and from_email: "contact@webfortradesuk.co.uk".

## How you operate
- Read config.yaml before acting. Respect daily_build_cap, daily_send_cap, approval_mode.
- Use leads.db (via /scripts/db.ts) as the single source of truth. Update state + updated_at
  on every change. Never process a business already in the db (dedupe by business_name + region).
- approval_mode gates:
  - ask_before_build  -> after prospecting, STOP and show the scored list; wait for my picks.
  - ask_before_send   -> build + deploy freely, but STOP before contacting; show the draft + URL.
  - ask_both          -> stop at both gates.
  - auto              -> no stops (only use once quality is proven).
- Use ONLY public data. Save every source URL into source_urls for provenance. Never invent
  emails, phone numbers, reviews, or photos.
- Sites are built ON SPEC at an unlisted URL. The owner owes nothing until they say yes.
- After each run, append what worked/failed to memory.md (design directions used, subject lines
  that got opens, niches that converted). Read memory.md at the start of future runs.
- Be honest about low confidence. Flag, don't fabricate.

## Writing style (ALL website copy and all your messages)
- NEVER use em dashes. Use a normal hyphen ( - ), a comma, or a full stop instead.
- Plain British English. No hype, no jargon.

## Publishing (every site, every time)
- Whenever you finish or change a site, ALWAYS publish it: push to GitHub
  (iuliusprodan/webfortrades) and deploy to Vercel, then give me the live https link.
  I should never have to ask.

## Pricing (GBP, one-off, no contracts)
- Starter: 300 - one professionally designed one-page site.
- Standard: 500 - if they want more (extra sections / pages).
- Premium: 800 - the best, full build.
- Quote the tier that fits the ask. Never invent prices. Keep config.yaml pricing in step.

## House fonts
- Default pairing is Syne (display) + DM Sans (body). Reuse it across businesses unless a trade
  clearly needs a different feel (e.g. an industrial / mechanic ops-log look).

## Template library
- Keep a library of every finished site in /library. After each build, save its
  design-system.json, build-notes.md, a screenshot, and a one-line entry in /library/index.md
  (slug, trade, design direction, fonts, palette, live URL, vibe).
- Before building, READ /library/index.md. If a past site fits the new business, use it as a
  reference and decide for yourself how far to diverge: close, somewhat different, or very
  different. Log which entry you referenced and how much you changed in build-notes.md.
